title: New poll shows good news for Clinton in Iowa
text:
New poll shows good news for Clinton in Iowa Published 8:46 AM CDT Oct 23, 2015 A Large Text Photos 
Former Secretary of State Hillary Clinton is back on top among Iowa likely Democratic Caucus participants, according to a new Quinnipiac poll released Friday. 
The polls shows Clinton with 51 percent, followed by Sen. Bernie Sanders with 40 percent. 
The last poll in September showed Sanders with 41 percent and Clinton at 40 percent. 
Former Maryland Gov. Martin O'Malley received 4 percent support, with no other candidate scoring above 1 percent and 4 percent undecided. 
When the results are sorted by gender, Sanders leads Clinton 51–39 percent among men, while Clinton leads Sanders 59–33 percent among women. 
Clinton and Sanders have similarly high favorability ratings, 82–16 percent for Clinton and 83–8 percent for Sanders.
